  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "2 Kings 23:14. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Kings 23:14",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And filled their places — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The places of the groves; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "with the bones of men — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Of the idolatrous priests, which he caused to be taken out of their graves, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Kings 23:18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". As he carried the ashes of the images to the graves, to mingle them with dead men’s bones, so he carried dead men’s bones to the places where the images had been, that both ways idolatry might be rendered loathsome. Dead men and dead gods were indeed much alike, and fittest to go together.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
